<HL>
   Who's News:
   Spectrum Control Taps
   Johnston as President
</HL>
<DATE>
04/06/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B12
</SO>
<CO>
   SPEC WNEWS
</CO>
<LP>
   ERIE, Pa. -- J.L. Johnston was named president and chief
executive officer of Spectrum Control Inc., an ailing maker
of electromagnetic products.
   The 47-year-old executive succeeds Thomas L. Venable, 55,
who remains chairman. Mr. Johnston previously was vice
president and general manager of the Electronic Components
division, Allen Bradley Co., a unit of Rockwell International
Corp.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Noting that Mr. Johnston has more than 20 years experience
in Spectrum's industry, Mr. Venable said: "He knows the
customers we serve and the product categories in which we
participate. We're confident that he will help return
Spectrum to profitability."
   In the nine months ended Aug. 31, Spectrum posted a net
loss of $665,000 on sales of $23.2 million.
</TEXT>
